summaries.short: Writer Michelle McNamara finds a new obsession in a California cold case she dubs the "Golden State Killer."
summaries.full: Writer Michelle McNamara, author of True Crime Diary, her blog about unsolved crimes, finds a new obsession in the "East Area Rapist" (EAR), who terrorized California in the 1970s and '80s and was, ultimately, responsible for 50 home-invasion rapes and 12 murders. Today, her husband, friends, and colleagues reflect on Michelle's talent for bringing true crime stories to life.

titles.full: The Sounds of Suburbia (with Liz Garbus and Elizabeth Wolff)

summaries.short: Directors Liz Garbus and Elizabeth Wolff join Nancy Miller to discuss their work on the series.
summaries.full: Nancy Miller sits down with series director Academy Award-nominee and Emmy Award-winner Liz Garbus and director/producer Elizabeth Wolff to talk about the responsibility they felt in doing justice to Michelle McNamara's work, their own backgrounds and sensitivities they brought to the series and the ways in which Michelle's work informed the filmmaking process.

summaries.short: Michelle reflects on the murder case that sparked her interest in true crime.
summaries.full: Michelle reflects on the 1984 murder of her childhood neighbor Kathy Lombardo, which she credits with planting the seed for her lifelong fascination with unsolved crimes. Local detectives who worked the EAR case in the '70s - and citizen detectives who picked up where they left off - discuss a proliferation of serial rape cases in Northern California at the time.

summaries.short: The brutal predator moves south, where he commits a series of gruesome murders. Michelle struggles to inject her own story into her book.
summaries.full: In 1979, law enforcement is thrilled when the EAR attacks abruptly stop in Northern California, but in reality, the still unknown assailant has moved south to commit a number of gruesome murders in the Santa Barbara area, known as the "Original Night Stalker" series. Michelle's article chronicling her investigation of the case causes a splash when it's published in 2013.

titles.full: Mrs. Brady with a Badge (with Carol Daly and Kim Stewart)

summaries.short: Retired Detective Carol Daly and Sheriff Kim Stewart meet for the first time on a call with Nancy Miller.
summaries.full: Retired Detective Carol Daly and Sheriff Kim Stewart meet for the first time on a call with Nancy Miller. The three talk about law enforcement practices before and after EAR/ONS, their experiences as women in the field, and where they were when the GSK was caught.

summaries.short: After gaining access to a treasure trove of case files, Michelle struggles to balance the demands of her work with her family life.
summaries.full: Michelle and her editors agree to push her book deadline after being granted access to the Orange County Sheriff's Department's East Area Rapist / Original Night Stalker (EAR/ONS) room. Overwhelmed by the amount of material and the graphic nature of the crimes, Michelle struggles to balance the demands of her self-described addiction to her work with her family life.
